\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We are a team of data scientists, business analysist, front-end developpers and full-stack developpers working on a GenAI hackathon leveraging GenAI and vibe coding tools to create innovative and high value web applications. For the hackathon we are focused on the following challenge stream: Solve real problems using City of Montgomery datasets, Civic Access & Community Communication. Moreover the goal would be to build tools that scrape live city updates, power resident-facing chatbots, and track sentiment or misinformation, like a \'93Service Finder\'94 combining open data with real-time web information. Help to brainstorm and get some ideas to start working. When brainstorming provide information as a chain of thought to be easily transformed in a user story to be then taken as input for development. based on Montgomery city publications what would be the most innovative apps to adress city issues focusing in services available and what is near me ?\
\
After reviewing several contextes we are aligned on the following user stories: \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 Looking at the context below create two user stories considering the context below and as technical backend netlify as a platform to deploy the application, brightdata for the backend data crawling and a RAG based LLM solution. Montgomery Civic Service Friction\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Core Problem: The disconnect and frustration caused by Montgomery's "Pull" system.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Feedback "Black Hole": The massive data disconnect (27k tracked vs ~700k actual) and the downstream effects (like uncollected garbage feeding the rat population).\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Solution (Two-Sided Platform):\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Part A (Citizens): GenAI answers, proactive push alerts, and auto-tagged 311 reporting.\
\ls1\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Part B (City Workers): Live dispatch dashboards and route optimization.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Business Case: Why the app wins (Call deflection, commerce protection, and restored trust).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The 4 Core Features ("Civic Copilot")\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Part A: For the Citizen\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 GenAI "Service Finder": A simple chat interface where residents can type or speak questions (e.g., "How do I pay my water bill?") and get instantly routed to the correct city resource.\
\ls3\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Dynamic "Push" Alerts: Uses the resident's zip code to send proactive phone notifications about local road closures or sudden changes to sanitation schedules before they occur.\
\ls3\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Frictionless "Snap & Submit" 311 Reporting: Citizens can take a photo of a pothole or missed trash, and the app auto-tags the GPS coordinates to submit a perfect ticket to the city.\
\ls3\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The "Close the Loop" Tracker: Automated status updates sent directly to the user's phone when their ticket is scheduled for repair and ultimately completed.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Part B: For the Service Provider (City Workers) 5. Live Dispatch Dashboard & Route Optimization: Sanitation drivers and public works crews log into the backend to see a live heatmap of citizen-submitted GPS photos. They use this live "overview" to optimize their routes and ensure they never miss clusters of garbage bins or hazards again. This directly triggers the "ticket closed" update to the citizen with a single tap.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

